            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server. It is designed to convert a numeric value into a string representation using the overpunch technique, which is a method used in mainframe systems to represent negative numbers in a compact form. This function is typically used in financial systems where data interchange with mainframe systems is required."
